{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/appendicitis/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"604d9119-1816-5321-bb8f-06e7ed2673e6","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 5afb155a-dac2-4fde-bb81-a7f20187988d --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 5afb155a-dac2-4fde-bb81-a7f20187988d -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item f8374ddd-45af-473b-a828-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field d4ae68f6-ffad-45c8-be68-a7f20187988d --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field d4ae68f6-ffad-45c8-be68-a7f20187988d --><!-- begin field 36998807-0ea8-4c03-a531-a7f20187988d --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 36998807-0ea8-4c03-a531-a7f20187988d --><!-- begin field a41e9a91-6d91-43c8-8693-a7f20187988d --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field a41e9a91-6d91-43c8-8693-a7f20187988d --><!-- begin field 5748d0e8-b213-45dc-9d1b-a7f20187988d --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 5748d0e8-b213-45dc-9d1b-a7f20187988d --><!-- begin field 13b57fcb-443a-4655-92d4-a7f20187988d --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field 13b57fcb-443a-4655-92d4-a7f20187988d --><!-- begin field 121873d4-31c7-4bab-9f18-a7f20187988d --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 121873d4-31c7-4bab-9f18-a7f20187988d --><!-- end item f8374ddd-45af-473b-a828-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"34a7018e-bdb2-5fb9-8f39-14b87cb77872","topicId":"38888cc0-af2f-4224-93a9-2ffe35d3793c","topicName":"Appendicitis","slug":"appendicitis","lastRevised":"Last revised in July 2020","chapters":[{"id":"c3867ccc-2088-5ea2-a8b8-c8a8fa3b1495","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"cadf0862-729f-56ee-b5c8-c92c5a72cbb5","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"efd5c1ac-3b3a-5b2c-82d5-19cda81e37fe","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"5c0768a7-4653-5b13-9bdd-b0696c5ea29a","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"1c4d3384-d57f-500b-ac6c-5360cef5f665","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"665f1a5d-97d4-56f8-a6d9-9fccc1bb162b","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"2b7bc994-71ff-5c70-9d2d-e88756d8ebeb","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"6546ce13-0da8-59ad-8062-384d7dc545ec","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"8fd8907b-64f5-5949-a722-c92fde97c4e7","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"